==English==

===Etymology===
From ''[[Bolshevik]]'', the socialist party in the 1918 Russian Revolution, from Russian ''Bolsheviki'', "majority faction"

===Adjective===
'''bolshie'''
# A [[derogatory]] word used in Britain, during the Cold War period to refer to [[communist|communists]], [[socialist|socialists]], labour union leaders and other leftists in the government

# An upstart. A difficult or rebellious person.

